Key Concepts
* [cite_start]`Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC)`: The primary interface for object management.
* [cite_start]`Organizational Units (OUs)`: Containers used to organize objects and link Group Policies.
* [cite_start]`Security Groups`: Objects used to assign permissions to multiple users simultaneously.
* [cite_start]`Domain Authentication`: The process of a client machine validating credentials against a Domain Controller.

Lessons Learned
* [cite_start]Effective organization in AD simplifies administrative tasks as the environment scales.
* [cite_start]Testing the end-user experience is a vital part of the provisioning process.

